CCD207-01 PATTERNS (MHz) Newton with LTC2207 A/D
-----------------
This pattern uses the 4H channel with 4 speeds of 5MHz, 3MHz, 1MHz and 50kHz.
2 Phase Vertical Clocking Scheme
Sequence is I1(2), I3(4) down towards the shift reg.
Image 3(4) is last row before shift reg.
Charge is transfered into R1 and R2 with R3 aligned with channel stops.
Conventional Clocking Sequence is: ...R3, R2, R1, R3, OG, Node
EM Gain Register Clcoking Sequence is ...R3, R1, R2DC(Virtual Phase at 2.5V), R2HV, R3, OG, Node
S1 to S4	Storage area clks
I1 to I4	Image area clks
B	Engine branch bit
SB1 to SB4	Engine loop speed bits. (Not applicable to Vertical Shift Routines) 
               For n = 0 Hold = 1; 
               For 0 - n - 8 Hold = (2^(n-1)) + 1;
               For 8 - n - 00   Hold = (256*(n-1))+1;
RST	CCD reset
PEN            KHz Sample clock used specifically for MAX1133ACAP A/D (Not used on New Newton Platform)
HVF	EMCCD HV falling edge (Only applicable on CCD-207 sensors)
AMP	Input amp restore
DSR            KHz Dual Slope Integrator Reset Pulse (Not used on New Newton Platform)
HVR	EMCCD HV rising edge (Only applicable on CCD-207 sensors)
CDS	Clamp to Ground	
R1 to R3	Horz register clks
MUX	Mux between analog channels
DSP            KHz Dual Slope Integrator Positive Pulse (Not used on New Newton Platform)
FIR	FIRE engine output - This is overwritten by software
DSN            KHz Dual Slope Integrator Negative Pulse (Not used on New Newton Platform)
PA1            Pre amp gain 1 overide
FRA	FRAME engine output - This is overwritten by software
RS	Reset sample (D-CDS)
SS	Signal sample (D-CDS); USB keep quiet
OSK	OS kill (stop CCD output amp glow) - Switches VOD off
CG2	Clamp-to-ground on analog channel 2 (Not used on Newton)
PA2	Pre amp gain 2 overide
PXL	Valid output pixel clk (USED AS A SDRAM SUPPRESSION SIGNAL)
SW	Summing well clk (Not Used on Newton as this is simply fed with R3 Clock)
SHU            SHUTTER engine output - This is overwritten by software
SSK            VSS Kill - Switches VSS OFF

-----------------

Turning off horz clocks during exposure at higher speeds to
stop 'background dark signal' and 'glow'.

P01 - CS 15/01/10
      First Pattern for CCD207-01 sensor in Newton platform with new LTC2207 A/D 
P02 - CS 07/04/10
      CDS Clock pulse increased to 3 line duration for both 1MHz and 3MHz readout speeds to resolve
      issue with switch not being activated
P03 - CS 11/10/10
      3MHz patterns re-optimised to improve vertical striping noise evident in image mode.
P04 - CS 28/02/11
      3MHz patterns re-optimised to improve vertical striping noise in image mode for 
      both em and conv amps. R2HV Rising and falling edges also limited to 2lines pulse 
      width and turned off for exp and vert routines. Exp routine changed to 5 lines to help
      Witec Accumulated noise issue, and HV and VH routines made to be the same with a duration
      of 2us to help diagonal noise patterns and to adhere to datasheet recommendations. 50kHz
      routines changes to equal 1600 hold lines.
P05 - CS 23/12/11
      PXL bit column used as a suppression signal for all SDRAM transfers. This is to resolve issues
      observed by Witec. Patterns re-optimised to improve image quality with new FPGA solution for Witec
      issues.
P06 - CS 17/01/12
      Patterns have been adjusted slightly to improve noise quality. 50kHz Conventional Mode changed to 1600
      hold lines.
